1
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:15,100
<i> I heard from Colonel Sarabia</i>

2
00:00:15,233 --> 00:00:17,900
<i>that an autopsy was done
on Joel's remains.</i>

3
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:21,033
<i>They checked the vials
and the syringe used.</i>

4
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:23,567
<i>Joel's fingerprints
were the only ones found.</i>

5
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:24,800
<i> Which probably means...</i>

6
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:27,033
<i>No. That's impossible!
He couldn't have done that.</i>

7
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:29,967
<i>He's not that kind of person,
Mom.</i>

8
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:31,733
<i> He couldn't do it.</i>

9
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:34,933
<i>This is the video Joel sent me
before he went to the restroom.</i>

10
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:37,133
<i>So Hazel was in the hospital
that day.</i>

11
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:39,133
<i>Could she have something to do
with what happened to Joel?</i>

12
00:00:39,267 --> 00:00:40,433
<i> You killed Joel, didn't you?</i>

13
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:43,700
<i>Why would I waste my time
on someone like Joel?</i>

14
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,133
<i> He meant nothing to me.</i>

15
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:46,333
<i> We have a video?</i>

16
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:48,200
<i>They didn't recognize
you anyway.</i>

17
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:49,800
<i> Maybe we should stop this.</i>

18
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:51,600
<i>What about justice for Jessica?</i>

19
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:55,267
<i>Even in death, you're still
going to abandon her?</i>

20
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,267
Don't!

21
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,333
Joel!

22
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:03,233
What were you doing?

23
00:02:03,367 --> 00:02:05,867
You scared me.
How did you get in?

24
00:02:07,033 --> 00:02:08,300
The door was open.

25
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:12,400
So, what's the news?

26
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:13,633
From Felma's house?

27
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,400
Aside from suspecting you,

28
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:20,700
they told Jeffrey about
what happened to Joel.

29
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,833
That's it?

30
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:26,467
That's not exactly solid info.

31
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:30,100
And what about Jeffrey?
Turns out he's far away.

32
00:02:31,367 --> 00:02:32,833
What's your plan?

33
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:34,367
You're going to kill him, too?

34
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,867
Why that tone?

35
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,500
It's just hard.

36
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:46,100
When Felma and her family
talk about Joel,

37
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:48,533
I feel a sense of guilt.

38
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:52,433
When it's Jessica, I get angry.

39
00:02:52,567 --> 00:02:55,767
But when they say they love
my child,

40
00:02:57,033 --> 00:02:58,467
I soften.

41
00:02:59,867 --> 00:03:03,133
I'm confused.
I don't know what the truth is.

42
00:03:04,700 --> 00:03:09,633
You're confused because you're
listening to everyone.

43
00:03:09,767 --> 00:03:11,233
Listen only to me.

44
00:03:11,367 --> 00:03:13,433
I'm the only one telling
the truth.

45
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,900
By any means necessary,

46
00:03:17,033 --> 00:03:19,400
we have to get justice
for Jessica.

47
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,800
Want some tea?

48
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:31,100
Mom, let me talk to Andrea.

49
00:03:31,233 --> 00:03:32,567
I'm sorry, son.

50
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:37,233
Your sister is still grieving.

51
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:39,133
Mom, maybe I should just
go home.

52
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:41,567
But you're still on vacation.

53
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:45,233
And you just got to spend time
again with Daisy and Tetay.

54
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:47,500
Coleen, I can't enjoy
myself here

55
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,533
while you're all struggling
back home.

56
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:50,867
I don't want that.

57
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,367
No, we can handle it, son.
We're helping each other.

58
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,767
Dad, we're family.

59
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:56,633
You said it yourself.

60
00:03:56,767 --> 00:04:00,233
We face problems together.

61
00:04:00,367 --> 00:04:01,767
And I believe

62
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:04,333
Hazel had something to do
with Joel's death.

63
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:06,400
And with what happened
to my sister.

64
00:04:06,533 --> 00:04:08,267
That's why I'm going home.

65
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:11,400
I'll find evidence and put
that woman in jail.

66
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:21,967
It's a good thing that their
eldest is coming home.

67
00:04:24,033 --> 00:04:25,367
So what's the plan?

68
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,500
<i> Come out here!</i>

69
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:31,467
What...

70
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,733
Who is it?

71
00:04:40,933 --> 00:04:42,800
Hazel!

72
00:04:42,933 --> 00:04:44,100
Hazel!

73
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,633
What do we do now?

74
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:51,767
She can't see you here.

75
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,700
Hazel!

76
00:05:02,633 --> 00:05:04,367
Come out here!

77
00:05:07,467 --> 00:05:08,967
What?

78
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,333
You again?

79
00:05:13,467 --> 00:05:14,600
What's your problem now?

80
00:05:14,733 --> 00:05:17,733
You! You're my problem!
Because you're a liar!

81
00:05:17,867 --> 00:05:19,733
You won't admit
you had something to do

82
00:05:19,867 --> 00:05:21,800
with Joel's death!

83
00:05:21,933 --> 00:05:24,033
Enough!

84
00:05:24,167 --> 00:05:26,000
We've been over this again
and again.

85
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,433
I already told you and Manuel

86
00:05:27,567 --> 00:05:29,400
that I had nothing to do with
what you're accusing me of.

87
00:05:29,533 --> 00:05:31,867
Leave. Or do you want my lawyer
to prove it to you?

88
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,867
Fine! Call your lawyer!

89
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,200
Have him come here!
Let's face each other!

90
00:05:35,367 --> 00:05:36,900
Wait...

91
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:38,700
What's wrong with you?
You can't go in there.

92
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:39,500
You're trespassing!

93
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:42,567
- Ouch! Hey!
- Come on, leave!

94
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,133
I said leave!

95
00:05:44,267 --> 00:05:46,167
You're not allowed inside!

96
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:49,400
This is my house! Get out!

97
00:05:51,867 --> 00:05:53,367
What? Leave already!

98
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,333
Why? Are you hiding something
inside?

99
00:05:55,467 --> 00:05:57,400
Is that why you won't let me in?

100
00:05:57,533 --> 00:05:58,900
- Is that it?
- What?

101
00:05:59,033 --> 00:05:59,933
What are you talking about?

102
00:06:00,067 --> 00:06:01,467
Of course, I won't let you in.
It's my house!

103
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,033
You don't have any say in that.
Just leave!

104
00:06:03,167 --> 00:06:05,700
- Let go of me!
- Hey! Andrea!

105
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:10,533
Wait! Hey, Andrea!
Wait a second!

106
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:11,533
- Hey!
- Who are you hiding in there?

107
00:06:11,667 --> 00:06:12,733
What is wrong with you?

108
00:06:12,867 --> 00:06:14,133
Why are you doing this?

109
00:06:14,267 --> 00:06:16,000
What are you even doing here?

110
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:18,033
Call your lawyer already!
Where is he?

111
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:20,633
Didn't you say you wanted
to prove you had nothing to do

112
00:06:20,767 --> 00:06:21,900
with Joel's death?

113
00:06:22,033 --> 00:06:22,933
Then do it!

114
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,967
Get out of here!
You've got some nerve!

115
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:26,267
I'm not leaving!

116
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:29,500
Tell me who the man
in that video is.

117
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,300
Who is he?

118
00:06:38,933 --> 00:06:40,100
Andeng?

119
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:43,733
Andeng?

120
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:44,733
Manuel.

121
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,300
Let her be.

122
00:06:49,433 --> 00:06:52,000
This is the first time Andeng
ever loved.

123
00:06:53,533 --> 00:06:57,033
Joel was the only one
she let into her heart

124
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:59,067
and into her life.

125
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,933
That's why this hurts me
even more.

126
00:07:03,367 --> 00:07:04,967
Just imagine.

127
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:08,500
This was the first man
she trusted since...

128
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,533
since I left all of you.

129
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:16,067
And then this happens.

130
00:07:16,233 --> 00:07:21,433
If you really believe I had
something to do with Joel,

131
00:07:21,567 --> 00:07:26,533
aren't you scared I might do
something to you, too?

132
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,800
What? You're scared, aren't you?

133
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:36,833
So leave. Just go!

134
00:07:36,967 --> 00:07:38,767
I'm not leaving!

135
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:41,700
Where's your lawyer?
We've been here long enough!

136
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,400
You don't order me around.

137
00:07:43,533 --> 00:07:46,667
Why should I do what you're
telling me?

138
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:50,533
And besides, I don't owe you
proof of my innocence.

139
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:52,367
So get out of my house.

140
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,533
- Leave!
- Wait!

141
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:57,600
Why are you so desperate
to kick me out?

142
00:07:57,733 --> 00:08:01,233
Is the man from Joel's video
in there?

143
00:08:01,367 --> 00:08:03,233
You're hiding him here,
aren't you?

144
00:08:03,367 --> 00:08:04,033
What is he?

145
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:07,233
Your accomplice in killing Joel?

146
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,800
Why did you kill him?

147
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:13,233
He never did anything to you!

148
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,300
Why did you do it?

149
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:18,333
You're so evil!
You're a monster, Hazel!

150
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:22,233
- Stop it! Andrea!
- Have you no mercy?

151
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:28,300
Hey!

152
00:08:28,433 --> 00:08:30,500
- What are you doing?
- Ouch!

153
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:32,867
Get out of here!
I'll sue you for trespassing!

154
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,067
If anything, you're the ones
who wronged me!

155
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,233
Do you understand?

156
00:08:36,367 --> 00:08:39,233
Manuel left me because of you!
You killed Jessica!

157
00:08:39,367 --> 00:08:42,133
And you still have the nerve
to barge into my house?

158
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:43,867
Wait a second!

159
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:45,800
You're the trespasser!

160
00:08:45,933 --> 00:08:48,033
You were the first one
to enter our lives

161
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:50,567
when you stole my father!

162
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:53,467
You took my family away from me!

163
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,467
And Jessica?

164
00:08:56,600 --> 00:09:00,000
You're blaming her death on us?

165
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:01,933
That happened because of you!

166
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,967
Because of what you did!

167
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:07,667
Because you abused her and Dad!

168
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:08,533
It's because of you!

169
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:10,967
- Not us!
- What are you saying?

170
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:13,933
- Stop it! Get out!
- Ouch!

171
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:15,600
I told you to leave!

172
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:19,767
Hazel! Open this door!

173
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:26,667
What did she mean
that Jessica died

174
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,567
because of what you did
to Manuel?

175
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,167
Don't listen to her.

176
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:34,733
That woman's crazy.

177
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:45,000
Why did you go to Hazel's house?

178
00:09:45,133 --> 00:09:47,667
And alone, at that?

179
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:51,567
Didn't you realize
that was Hazel?

180
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:53,467
I'm not afraid of her, Mom.

181
00:09:55,233 --> 00:10:00,433
I feel nothing for that woman
except anger, especially now.

182
00:10:02,467 --> 00:10:04,900
Dear, don't go back there again.

183
00:10:05,033 --> 00:10:08,333
We don't know what Hazel
might do.

184
00:10:08,467 --> 00:10:11,033
I know exactly
what she's capable of, Dad.

185
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:18,000
She's capable of killing someone
just to get revenge.

186
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:21,033
Dad.

187
00:10:22,567 --> 00:10:24,533
Mom. She killed Joel.

188
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:28,333
She killed the man...

189
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,900
the man who stayed with me.

190
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:36,967
The man who truly loved me.

191
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:39,300
Dear,

192
00:10:39,433 --> 00:10:41,467
we're not sure about that.

193
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:44,167
I'm sure.

194
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:47,900
Joel was a good man.

195
00:10:49,467 --> 00:10:51,833
We all knew him.

196
00:10:51,967 --> 00:10:54,000
He would never hurt himself.

197
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:56,000
He could never do
that to himself.

198
00:10:57,767 --> 00:11:00,633
Mom, all I'm missing
is evidence.

199
00:11:00,767 --> 00:11:03,200
But I already have the truth.

200
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:07,467
I know Hazel killed Joel.

201
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,333
I won't stop

202
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:14,700
until she goes through
what she put Coleen through.

203
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:17,067
I'll pin the crime on her
and make her suffer.

204
00:11:18,367 --> 00:11:21,433
The only difference between her
and Coleen

205
00:11:21,567 --> 00:11:23,933
is that Coleen was innocent.

206
00:11:24,067 --> 00:11:27,833
Hazel is not.

207
00:11:29,267 --> 00:11:31,233
Andrea.

208
00:11:31,367 --> 00:11:36,033
Sweetie,
don't let anger consume you.

209
00:11:36,167 --> 00:11:38,800
Anger is all I have left, Mom.

210
00:11:38,933 --> 00:11:42,933
It's the only weapon I have.

211
00:11:44,233 --> 00:11:47,267
And I'll use it

212
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:54,367
to make sure I get justice
for what Hazel did to Joel.

213
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:07,700
Ma'am, I'm sorry,
I got here late.

214
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:10,267
I couldn't
just leave Southcrest.

215
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,933
It's fine.

216
00:12:12,067 --> 00:12:15,200
We'll adjust to your schedule.

217
00:12:15,367 --> 00:12:18,000
Whenever you're available.

218
00:12:18,133 --> 00:12:20,400
- Ma'am, please hold on here.
- Yes.

219
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,000
Is that so?

220
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,933
Is that all?

221
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:29,000
All right,
thank you very much.

222
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:31,433
Okay, Colonel,
thank you again.

223
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:33,400
Uncle Noah?

224
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:34,567
Yes, my dear?

225
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:39,300
Jeff said he's coming home
to be with Andrea.

226
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:42,500
Tell him not to, Coleen.

227
00:12:44,733 --> 00:12:48,933
Let him make the most of his
time with Daisy and Tetay.

228
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:52,933
Why? What can he even do
if he comes home?

229
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:56,500
Joel won't come back anyway.

230
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,567
Joel is gone.

231
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,733
By the way,

232
00:13:02,867 --> 00:13:04,767
Colonel Sarabia
has an update.

233
00:13:07,233 --> 00:13:09,233
The investigation team
is now checking

234
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:13,967
if the video is connected
to Hazel with that man

235
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:15,900
from Joel's recording.

236
00:13:16,033 --> 00:13:17,900
And if connected to his death.

237
00:13:18,033 --> 00:13:20,733
And they've officially
ruled out suicide.

238
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,367
As they should, Uncle.

239
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:23,800
As they should!

240
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:26,033
Joel wasn't a drug addict.

241
00:13:26,467 --> 00:13:27,833
He was murdered.

242
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:29,733
Hazel killed him.

243
00:13:30,533 --> 00:13:31,833
Dear, we'll hold her
accountable.

244
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:35,833
And the man she was talking
to in that video.

245
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:37,367
If he really is her accomplice.

246
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:42,267
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

247
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,033
Did I press too hard?

248
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,067
It's fine.

249
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:53,667
I'm just sad.

250
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,500
Because...

251
00:13:57,633 --> 00:14:01,633
two members of our family
in such a short time...

252
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:06,467
were taken away from us.

253
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:11,567
You're very kind.

254
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:15,867
Even if they weren't
blood-related,

255
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,600
you treated them as family.

256
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:29,533
You don't have to share blood
to be family.

257
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:34,867
I thought our family
was growing.

258
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:44,567
I was so happy when Joel and
Jessica came into our lives.

259
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:48,133
Especially Jessica.

260
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:53,733
I loved that child so much.

261
00:14:55,567 --> 00:14:58,200
We all did.

262
00:14:58,333 --> 00:15:00,733
We loved her.

263
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:09,667
- Coleen.
- Coleen, my child.

264
00:15:10,933 --> 00:15:13,267
It makes me so angry, Uncle.

265
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:16,800
In just one year,
I lost two people.

266
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:20,367
I lost a new older brother
and a younger sibling.

267
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:24,800
I didn't even get enough time
being Joel's little sister.

268
00:15:26,367 --> 00:15:28,100
And Jessica...

269
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:32,067
Dad, I didn't even get to be
a proper big sister to her.

270
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:36,700
I didn't even get to spoil her.

271
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:55,700
Alice.

272
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:06,433
Are you avoiding me?

273
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,400
No.

274
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:11,000
I've just been busy.

275
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:13,333
A lot of people took leave
at the same time.

276
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:17,267
Our duty schedule got messed up.

277
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,300
You're lying.

278
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,033
Okay.

279
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,167
You want the truth?

280
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,367
I'm distancing myself.

281
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:31,433
I'm scared I'll get dragged
into what you did, Hazel.

282
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:34,233
You're getting worse and worse.

283
00:16:34,367 --> 00:16:36,067
I can't handle it anymore.

284
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:39,633
I might get involved
and lose my job.

285
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:41,867
You're overreacting.

286
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:43,500
Stop being so dramatic.

287
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:48,300
Sorry, but I feel guilty now.

288
00:16:48,433 --> 00:16:50,867
I told you, I don't want
something like this.

289
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,733
Hazel, you've gone too far.

290
00:16:53,867 --> 00:16:56,200
You don't get to avoid me.

291
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:03,600
Try to run, and my temper
will escalate, too.

292
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:09,233
If you try to drag me down,

293
00:17:09,367 --> 00:17:12,167
you should already know me
by now, right?

294
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:14,567
You know what I'm capable of.

295
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,800
No matter who it is.

296
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:31,533
Andrea?

297
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:32,833
What happened to you?

298
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:35,500
I heard you asked for me.

299
00:17:35,633 --> 00:17:36,900
I'm not sick.

300
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:39,967
I just wanted to talk.

301
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:42,700
Andrea, we're in the ER.

302
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:44,467
Exactly.

303
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,000
You can't escape.

304
00:17:48,933 --> 00:17:50,667
Tell me, Alice.

305
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:54,233
What do you know
about Joel's death?

306
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:56,900
Were you Hazel's accomplice?

307
00:17:58,367 --> 00:17:59,633
What?

308
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:01,033
Admit it.

309
00:18:02,433 --> 00:18:04,200
Let's get ahead
of the investigation.

310
00:18:05,633 --> 00:18:07,900
So I won't have to include you
in the lawsuit.

311
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,733
Hi, sweetie.

312
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:20,700
I'm sorry.

313
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,733
Mommy's...

314
00:18:25,133 --> 00:18:26,467
a little tipsy.

315
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:30,533
I'm just happy.

316
00:18:30,867 --> 00:18:34,100
Because, as of now,

317
00:18:34,233 --> 00:18:39,433
your daddy and his other family
are being rattled.

318
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:58,533
This is just between
you and me, ha?

319
00:18:58,700 --> 00:18:59,867
Sweetie.

320
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:06,267
Did you know?

321
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:15,933
Your Papa Jojo and I killed
Andrea's man.

322
00:19:21,367 --> 00:19:22,833
Yes.

323
00:19:26,233 --> 00:19:28,733
He was such a show-off!

324
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:30,533
Always trying to be the hero.

325
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:33,667
He said he'd expose us.

326
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,167
That he'd tell Felma everything.

327
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:38,500
Of course, I couldn't let
that happen, right?

328
00:19:38,633 --> 00:19:40,967
What choice did I have?

329
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:43,167
I acted first.

330
00:19:46,967 --> 00:19:56,533
We can't let our revenge fail
after what they did to you.

331
00:19:58,367 --> 00:20:02,767
You were my only child.

332
00:20:04,567 --> 00:20:09,833
The only one who truly loved me.

333
00:20:12,067 --> 00:20:13,433
It was only you, my child.

334
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:14,900
Only you.

335
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:17,233
Only you.

336
00:20:17,367 --> 00:20:20,033
I love you so much, my child.

337
00:20:20,167 --> 00:20:22,567
But how could I ever
show it to you?

338
00:20:23,733 --> 00:20:25,367
You're gone.

339
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:28,500
But don't worry.

340
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:30,167
I already have a plan.

341
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,567
I'll go after them one by one.

342
00:20:39,367 --> 00:20:41,800
One by one.

343
00:20:45,367 --> 00:20:48,500
One by one...

344
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,300
My, child, sweetie.

345
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:58,633
Andrea, don't waste the ER's
time if you're not sick.

346
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:02,300
Have some respect
for the real patients.

347
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:03,633
Please.

348
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:09,267
- Ouch!
- Don't turn your back on me.

349
00:21:11,267 --> 00:21:12,533
Let go of me!

350
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:13,800
You're not getting
anything from me.

351
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:15,800
I won't tell you a thing.

352
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:18,333
You won't say anything?

353
00:21:18,467 --> 00:21:19,967
So that means
you do know something.

354
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:21,967
Leave!

355
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,133
Alice, I hope you don't tolerate

356
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:26,267
your friend's evilness.

357
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:27,600
Can you just leave already?

358
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:30,200
Guard!

359
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:32,500
There's someone here
pretending to be a patient.

360
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:34,300
She doesn't have
any medical issues.

361
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:37,967
- Ma'am?
- I'm not causing trouble.

362
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,333
I'm leaving.

363
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:47,533
But I hope, Alice,
you grow a conscience.

364
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:50,633
Your friend has already
killed someone.

365
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,200
And don't deny it

366
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,367
because we both know...

367
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:59,733
Hazel killed Joel.

368
00:21:59,867 --> 00:22:01,233
And you know it.

369
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:03,533
You know that.

370
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:17,567
What happened?

371
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:24,533
Are you still okay

372
00:22:24,667 --> 00:22:27,133
with everything Hazel's
ordering you to do?

373
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,000
Yes.

374
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,633
I'm angry at Manuel's family.

375
00:22:31,667 --> 00:22:33,733
Are you sure?

376
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:36,067
Because I see something else
in your eyes.

377
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:39,267
You're carrying Joel's death
with you.

378
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:40,933
You're guilty.

379
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:48,533
Yes.

380
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:50,600
I'll admit it.

381
00:22:51,967 --> 00:22:54,433
I thought I knew
what I was doing.

382
00:22:55,633 --> 00:22:56,967
This revenge.

383
00:22:59,033 --> 00:23:00,500
I was all for it.

384
00:23:02,033 --> 00:23:06,333
I wanted payback against
the family of the man

385
00:23:06,467 --> 00:23:10,033
who betrayed Hazel
and killed my child.

386
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:13,433
But this isn't what I expected.

387
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:18,800
I didn't know Hazel
was capable of...

388
00:23:20,767 --> 00:23:22,067
of killing someone.

389
00:23:24,567 --> 00:23:25,633
But...

390
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:30,367
my desire to avenge Jessica
still outweighs everything.

391
00:23:32,267 --> 00:23:35,200
I will never forgive Manuel...

392
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:37,767
and his family for what they did
to my child.

393
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:41,033
Jojo, there's something
you need to know.

394
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:46,467
Wait.

395
00:23:48,033 --> 00:23:49,633
Yes, friend?

396
00:23:49,767 --> 00:23:51,033
<i> Hi, Alice.</i>

397
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:53,500
<i>What are you and Jojo
talking about?</i>

398
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:55,033
<i> Care to share?</i>

399
00:23:57,767 --> 00:24:00,000
<i> Why did you suddenly go quiet?</i>

400
00:24:01,767 --> 00:24:03,667
<i> Remember, Alice.</i>

401
00:24:04,067 --> 00:24:06,967
<i> I have eyes for you, friend.</i>

402
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:09,033
<i> So be careful.</i>

403
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:11,667
<i> Be very, very careful.</i>

404
00:24:13,367 --> 00:24:14,167
Alice.

405
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,900
What was it you needed
to tell me?

406
00:24:18,033 --> 00:24:19,567
What?

407
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:21,033
Nothing, Jojo.

408
00:24:21,167 --> 00:24:22,700
I have to go.

409
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:26,233
Alice.

410
00:24:35,567 --> 00:24:36,933
Why don't you stay
a little longer?

411
00:24:37,067 --> 00:24:39,800
Mom, Dad, Daisy already booked
my ticket.

412
00:24:39,933 --> 00:24:41,133
All right then,
when are you heading home?

413
00:24:41,267 --> 00:24:42,867
What time's your flight?

414
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,000
This Saturday.

415
00:24:44,133 --> 00:24:45,133
Do you already know
where you're going?

416
00:24:45,267 --> 00:24:46,133
Yes, Ma'am.

417
00:24:46,267 --> 00:24:47,367
So who's the target?

418
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:48,533
It's him.

419
00:24:51,833 --> 00:24:52,967
What is this?

420
00:24:53,100 --> 00:24:54,833
Who are you??
I don't know you!

421
00:24:54,967 --> 00:24:56,633
Dad! Dad!
Uncle!
